Module kleve.testtwo

Class MainController

java.lang.Object
kleve.testtwo.controllers.MainController
All Implemented Interfaces:
javafx.fxml.Initializable
public class MainController extends Object implements javafx.fxml.Initializable
This class is the controller for the Main menu. It populates the tableviews with data via initialize and gives functionality to the buttons via methods.

    • onProductSearchText

      public void onProductSearchText(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
      This method updates the product tableview by filtering it.
      Parameters:
      actionEvent - This method is called when the user presses enter in the search field above the product tableview. First the method takes the text from the search field and determines if it can be parsed as an integer. If it can be parsed as an integer, it then looks up the product by the id integer. If it cannot be parsed as an integer, it then looks up the product by name using the string from the search field. The method then checks if no results were found and if so, outputs a warning message. The method then refreshes the table view to show the list of matching products. RUNTIME ERROR: The condition in the last if statement had to be changed from checking == null to .isEmpty(). This is because the list is initialized as an observable array list which is not considered == null even though it is empty.

    • onPartSearchText

      public void onPartSearchText(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
      This method updates the part tableview by filtering it.
      Parameters:
      actionEvent - This method is called when the user presses enter in the search field above the part tableview. First the method takes the text from the search field and determines if it can be parsed as an integer. If it can be parsed as an integer, it then looks up the part by the id integer. If it cannot be parsed as an integer, it then looks up the part by name using the string from the search field. The method then checks if no results were found and if so, outputs a warning message. The method then refreshes the table view to show the list of matching parts.

    • onModifyPartButtonClick

      public void onModifyPartButtonClick(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent) throws IOException
      This method stores the selected part in a static variable then opens the modify part menu.
      Parameters:
      actionEvent - This method is called when the modify button under the part tableview is clicked.
      Throws:
      IOException - The method can throw this error as it can fail to locate or load resources when opening a new scene. First it checks if a part is selected in the tableview, exiting the method if no part is selected. Next it takes the selected part and determines if it is an in house or outsourced part. Then it sets the static selectedInHouse or selectedOutsourced variable to the selected part and sets the other static variable to null to prevent errors.

    • onModifyProductButtonClick

      public void onModifyProductButtonClick(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent) throws IOException
      This method opens the modify product menu.
      Parameters:
      actionEvent - This method is called when the modify button under the product tableview is clicked.
      Throws:
      IOException - The method can throw this error as it can fail to locate or load resources when opening a new scene. It first checks if a product is selected, giving a warning message if no product is selected and exiting the method. Then it sets the selected product from the tableview as the static selectedProduct variable so the other menu can access that data.

    • onPartDeleteButtonClick

      public void onPartDeleteButtonClick(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
      This method deletes the selected part from the allParts list and therefore the part tableview.
      Parameters:
      actionEvent - This method is called when the delete button under the part tableview is clicked. It first checks if a part is selected in the tableview and exits if no part is selected. It then prompts the user to confirm they wish to delete the selected part, exiting without deleting if they select cancel.

    • onProductDeleteButtonClick

      public void onProductDeleteButtonClick(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
      This method deletes the selected product from the allProducts list and therefore the product tableview.
      Parameters:
      actionEvent - This method is called when the delete button under the product tableview is clicked. It first checks if a product is selected in the tableview and exits if no product is selected. It next checks if the selected product has associated parts. If it does, it gives a warning message and does not proceed with deleting the part. It then prompts the user to confirm they wish to delete the selected product, exiting without deleting if they select cancel. RUNTIME ERROR: The prodToDel.getAssociatedParts() had to be changed from != null to ! ... .isEmpty() as creating a new part creates an initialized, not null associated parts list.
